item.title: Project IV: Intent and Entity classification Model
item.description: While the pensioner of Ghent and his eminence were exchanging very low bows and a few words in voices still lower, a man of lofty stature, with a large face and broad shoulders, presented himself, in order to enter abreast with Guillaume Rym; one would have pronounced him a bull-dog by the side of a fox. His felt doublet and leather jerkin made a spot on the velvet and silk which surrounded him.

item.title: Project III: Automatic Cheque Book Processing ( Ongoing )
item.description: Technology: python, flask, AWS, jupyter notebook, Machine Learning, Deep Learning, Computer Vission To build an automatic system where user will only upload the image of the cheque book and system will accept or reject based on the validation of all the fields in the Cheque Slip. Technologies used: Python, Tensor flow 2.x, Keras, PyQt, Appium, Selenium, OCR(Custom and prebuild both). Use various Image Preprocessing techniques on the initial image to get the better extraction of the data before passing to the OCR Manipulated the coordinates of the bounding box using OpenCV to get the better area of the Text.

item.title: Project II: Electronic Health Recognization[EHR]
item.description: Technology: python, flask, AWS, jupyter notebook, Machine Learning Early detection of any preventable diseases is important for better disease management, improved interventions, and more efficient health-care resource allocation. We have seen since past decade we witnessed a sky-rocketing increase of information in Electronic Health Record (EHR) systems. Structured patient information like demographics, disease history, lab results, procedures and medications. By our project we can detect the diseases.

item.title: Project VI: Esmeralda
item.description: We are delighted to be able to inform the reader, that during the whole of this scene, Gringoire and his piece had stood firm. His actors, spurred on by him, had not ceased to spout his comedy, and he had not ceased to listen to it. He had made up his mind about the tumult, and was determined to proceed to the end, not giving up the hope of a return of attention on the part of the public.

item.title: Project V: Quasimodo
item.description: In the twinkling of an eye, all was ready to execute Coppenoleâ€™s idea. Bourgeois, scholars and law clerks all set to work. A pane broken in the pretty rose window above the door, left free a circle of stone through which it was agreed that the competitors should thrust their heads.
